# Phase 2: Framework Setup

Establish processing framework before content generation.

## Objective

Set up all framework elements needed for parallel content generation, ensuring agents have consistent guidelines and shared context.

## Prerequisites

Phase 1 completed with user-approved processing plan.

## Tasks

### Terminology Standardization
- Define consistent terminology to use across all outputs
- Create terminology glossary if needed
- Document any translation or mapping of source terms

### Template Preparation
- Prepare output templates if applicable
- Define formatting standards
- Establish section structure for each output type

### Agent Coordination Setup
- Initialize CHECKLIST.md with all processing items
- Define agent assignment strategy
- Establish status update protocol

### Quality Framework
- Review verification standards in `/4-references/`
- Confirm quality criteria for outputs
- Prepare verification checklists

## Outputs

- `/2-work-in-progress/terminology.md` - Standardized terminology
- `/2-work-in-progress/CHECKLIST.md` - Updated with all items
- Quality framework confirmed and ready

